# MailoReply AI - Environment Configuration
#
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. Set all required variables below
# 2. Deploy the Supabase schema (supabase_schema_clean.sql)
# 3. Configure N8N webhooks
# 4. Run initial setup at /setup
#
# For development with demo mode, leave Supabase variables unset

# ==============================================
# BUILDER.IO (OPTIONAL)
# ==============================================
VITE_PUBLIC_BUILDER_KEY=__BUILDER_PUBLIC_KEY__

# ==============================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED FOR PRODUCTION)
# ==============================================
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key

# ==============================================
# N8N INTEGRATION (REQUIRED FOR AI GENERATION)
# ==============================================
# Set up two separate webhook URLs for AI generation
# VITE_N8N_REPLY_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-n8n-instance.com/webhook/ai-reply
# VITE_N8N_EMAIL_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-n8n-instance.com/webhook/ai-email
# VITE_N8N_WEBHOOK_TOKEN=your-webhook-authentication-token

# ==============================================
# DEMO MODE NOTICE
# ==============================================
# When Supabase variables are not set, the app runs in Demo Mode with:
# - Mock authentication (superuser@demo.com / demo123)
# - Sample usage data and templates
# - All features functional but data not persisted
#
# To enable production mode:
# 1. Uncomment and set Supabase variables above
# 2. Set up N8N webhooks for real AI generation
# 3. Deploy database schema and run /setup
